Apax May Buy $100 Million Stake in Jyothy, Standard Reports

-- B y   M a l a v i k a   S h a r m a
-- 
2011-04-21T04:55:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/apax-may-buy-100-million-stake-in-jyothy-standard-reports.html
Apax Partners LLP, a London-based
private equity firm, may spend as much as $100 million to buy a
10 to 12 percent stake in  Jyothy Laboratories Ltd. (JYL) , Business
Standard reported, citing people it didn’t identify.  The purchase will help Jyothy Laboratories finance the
acquisition of  Henkel AG ’s Indian brands, according to the
newspaper. Jyothy may complete talks on buying Henkel’s brands
in two weeks, according to the report.  after the company acquires  Henkel India Ltd. (HNKL) ,  To contact the reporter on this story:
Malavika Sharma in New Delhi at 
 msharma52@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Hari Govind at   hgovind@bloomberg.net  